ros%2C%20which%20is%20around%20%24320%2C%20a%20month%20for%20one%20child.%20Our%20income%20was%20at%20the%20higher%20end%2C%20so%20we%20paid%20full%20price%2C%20which%20was%20800%20euros%2C%20about%20%24860%2C%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20flexible%2C%20and%20the%20childminder%20would%20also%20take%20care%20of%20our%20daughter%20if%20she%20fell%20ill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EChildcare%20in%20the%20UK%20was%20expensive%20and%20hard%20to%20access%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20daughter%20was%2018%20months%20old%2C%20in%20August%202021%2C%20our%20family%20moved%20to%20Cambridge%20for%20my%20husband's%20job.%20I%20was%20able%20to%20transfer%20my%20job%20at%20a%20consultancy%20firm%20to%20the%20London%20office%20and%20work%20hybrid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcouldnt-afford-childcare-daughter-started-kindergarten-early-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChildcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20completely%20different%20in%20the%20UK%20from%20France.%20Even%20getting%20a%20spot%20in%20the%20nursery%20was%20difficult.%20There%20was%20only%20one%20nursery%20place%20available%20in%20the%20city.%20It%20was%20in%20the%20north%2C%20and%20we%20lived%20in%20the%20south.%20It%20was%20a%2045-minute%20drive%20each%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20my%20second%20child%20in%20April%202022.%20Both%20my%20children%20were%20in%20the%20same%20nursery.%20Full-time%20nursery%20care%20a%20month%20per%20child%20cost%20%C2%A31%2C400%2C%20which%20is%20about%20%241%2C700.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20had%20demanding%20jobs%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20have%20any%20childcare%20support%20apart%20from%20nursery.%20It%20was%20extremely%20hard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20system%20made%20it%20hard%20to%20manage%20childcare%20and%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20children%20were%20ill%2C%20they%20were%20sent%20home%20for%20two%20days%20under%20the%20nursery%20policy.%20Sometimes%2C%20they'd%20need%20to%20see%20a%20doctor%20before%20they%20were%20allowed%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20nursery.%20It%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20get%20doctor's%20appointments%20quickly%20in%20the%20UK.%20That%20made%20things%20complicated%20for%20us%20as%20working%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20in%20November%202021%2C%20when%20our%20daughter%20was%20ill%2C%20I%20had%20to%20cancel%20my%20meetings%20for%20a%20consulting%20project%20I%20was%20project%20managing%20to%20take%20her%20to%20get%20a%20COVID-19%20test.%20These%20consultancy%20projects%20are%20time-sensitive%2C%20and%20I%20was%20under%20pressure.%20For%20three%20days%2C%20I%20looked%20after%20our%20daughter%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20looked%20after%20her%20in%20the%20afternoon%20so%20I%20could%20go%20back%20to%20work.%20It%20was%20very%20stressful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESomething%20like%20that%20would%20happen%20every%20two%20or%20three%20weeks.%20I'd%20be%20on%20work%20calls%20and%20hear%20one%20of%20the%20children%20crying%20in%20the%20background.%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20wasn't%20working%20well%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20parenting%20well%2C%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20nursery%20would%20sometimes%20turn%20parents%20away%20at%20the%20door%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20there%20weren't%20enough%20nursery%20employees%20to%20look%20after%20all%20the%20children.%20The%20nursery%20employees%20would%20send%20a%20message%20to%20parents%20in%20the%20morning%20saying%20they%20could%20only%20take%20five%20children%20that%20day%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere'd%20be%20a%20line%20of%20parents%20waiting%20outside%20the%20nursery%2C%20and%20after%20the%20available%20places%20were%20filled%2C%20the%20parents%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20line%20would%20have%20to%20take%20their%20children%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20pretty%20harsh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20decided%20to%20move%20to%20Spain%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20liked%20the%20UK's%20entrepreneurial%20spirit%20and%20food%2C%20but%20we%20weren't%20happy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20was%20the%20childcare%20expensive%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20a%20very%20individualistic%20place%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbought-california-ghost-town-cerro-gordo-lonely-found-life-purpose-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eisolated%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20asked%20our%20neighbors%20in%20Cambridge%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20have%20dinner%2C%20and%20though%20they%20said%20yes%20several%20times%2C%20it%20never%20happened.%20In%20Spain%2C%20when%20you%20say%20you'll%20go%20for%20dinner%2C%20you%20set%20the%20date.%20Something%20like%20that%20seemed%20to%20happen%20in%20every%20single%20relationship%20that%20we%20had%20with%20British%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20moved%20to%20Madrid%20in%20August%202023.%20Childcare%20was%20a%20big%20factor%2C%20but%20we%20also%20wanted%20to%20be%20near%20my%20family%20and%20have%20more%20of%20a%20support%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20firm%20wouldn't%20let%20me%20transfer%20from%20London%20to%20Madrid%2C%20so%20I%20took%20voluntary%20redundancy.%20My%20biggest%20fear%20was%20that%20job%20opportunities%20would%20be%20more%20limited%20in%20Madrid%2C%20but%20I%20started%20a%20new%20job%20as%20a%20VP%20for%20an%20aviation%20company%20in%20April.%20I'm%20now%20earning%20more%20than%20I%20was%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20here%20seem%20healthier%2C%20and%20healthcare%20is%20easier%20to%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20quality%20of%20childcare%20is%20better%20and%20cheaper%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20youngest%20child%20is%20still%20in%20nursery%2C%20which%20is%20a%2010-minute%20walk%20from%20our%20home%2C%20and%20very%20flexible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20warmer%20and%20more%20caring%20toward%20children%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20though%20maybe%20it's%20just%20expressed%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20my%20son%20is%20a%20little%20ill%2C%20the%20nursery%20workers%20don't%20send%20him%20home%20immediately.%20Instead%2C%20they%20look%20after%20him.%20It%20feels%20like%20I'm%20leaving%20him%20with%20a%20family%20member%20%E2%80%94%20like%20a%20delegated%20maternal%20figure.%20I%20never%20felt%20like%20that%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20540%20euros%2C%20which%20is%20about%20%24580%2C%20a%20month%20for%20a%20full-time%20nursery%20for%20one%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20have%20home%20help%20too%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20worried%20about%20who%20would%20look%20after%20our%20daughter%2C%20who%20is%20at%20school%20if%20she%20fell%20ill.%20We%20hired%20someone%20to%20work%20at%20home%2C%20which%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20affordable%20in%20the%20UK.%20They%20manage%20cleaning%2C%20shopping%2C%20and%20childcare%20when%20needed.%20The%20help%20costs%20us%201%2C750%20euros%20a%20month%20for%2040%20hours%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20make%20things%20much%20easier%20%E2%80%94%20I%20realize%20we're%20very%20privileged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20nice%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-to-colorado-mountains-mistake-left-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enear%20family%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%20They%20don't%20help%20out%20that%20much%20with%20the%20childcare%20but%20it's%20good%20for%20the%20heart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-spain-for-more-affordable-childcare-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714554002000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662fc27a10dfcda40964791e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-spain-for-more-affordable-childcare-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Sara%20Bustillo%20de%20Castro%20moved%20from%20London%20to%20Madrid%20after%20she%20found%20the%20childcare%20too%20expensive%20and%20low%20quality%20in%20the%20UK.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ehopkins%40insider.com%20(Ella%20Hopkins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-moved-to-spain-for-more-affordable-childcare-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Black%20creators%20were%20instrumental%20in%20building%20TikTok.%20Now%20they%20fear%20they'll%20be%20hit%20the%20hardest%20by%20a%20ban.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Young%20TikTok%20creator%20dancing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662f790a10dfcda4096449ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBlack%20content%20creators%20may%20be%20most%20affected%20if%20TikTok%20is%20banned%20in%20the%20US%20(stock%20photo).%3Cp%3EHector%20Pertuz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20bill%20passed%20last%20week%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20unless%20ByteDance%20sells%20it%20to%20a%20US%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBlack%20creators%2C%20who%20were%20instrumental%20in%20the%20platform's%20growth%2C%20could%20be%20significantly%20affected.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETheir%20feelings%20are%20complicated%2C%20though%2C%20due%20to%20tensions%20with%20equal%20pay%20and%20credit%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20content%20creators%20were%20monumental%20in%20helping%20make%20TikTok%20into%20what%20it%20is%20today%2C%20but%20now%20they%20might%20be%20some%20of%20the%20most%20affected%20if%20the%20platform%20is%20banned%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Senate%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenate-passes-tiktok-ban-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epassed%20a%20bill%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20that%20could%20mean%20TikTok%20is%20removed%20from%20app%20stores%20in%20nine%20months%20unless%20its%20parent%20company%2C%20Bytedance%2C%20sells%20it%20to%20a%20US%20corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ceo-shou-chew-pressure-users-freak-out-ban-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esigned%20it%20into%20law%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20the%20clock%20is%20now%20ticking%20for%20ByteDance%20to%20give%20up%20its%20US%20TikTok%20assets%20or%20face%20a%20nationwide%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-black-content-creators-trying-to-lessen-influencer-pay-gap-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlack%20creators%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20said%20they%20feel%20they%20will%20be%20particularly%20affected%20if%20the%20ban%20goes%20ahead%20despite%20playing%20such%20a%20huge%20part%20in%20helping%20TikTok%20become%20what%20it%20is%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20support%20for%20TikTok%20is%20complicated.%20They%20say%20the%20app%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblack-tiktokers-influencers-millions-followers-side-gigs-monetization-challenges-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistorically%20been%20inconsistent%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F02%2F13%2Fstyle%2Fthe-original-renegade.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrediting%20Black%20creators%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20having%20faced%20allegations%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F09%2F21%2Ftech%2Ftiktok-black-employees-discrimination-legal-complaint%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoxicity%20and%20racism%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20inside%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20largely%2C%20TikTok%20is%20a%20place%20Black%20creators%20found%20where%20they%20could%20thrive%20and%20reach%20new%20audiences%20and%20customers%20for%20their%20growing%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20a%20TikTok%20ban%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bdevastating%26quot%3B%20to%20Black%20creators%2C%20Tenyse%20Williams%2C%20the%20CEO%20and%20founder%20of%20Verified%20Consulting%20and%20an%20adjunct%20instructor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Central%20Florida%2C%20Columbia%20University%2C%20and%20George%20Washington%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20have%20worked%20hard%20to%20build%20their%20followers%20and%20businesses%20on%20this%20platform%2C%20and%20losing%20it%20would%20mean%20starting%20over%20from%20scratch%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20losing%20a%20platform%2C%20but%20also%20rebuilding%20their%20digital%20homes%20and%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20democratization%20of%20influencing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFunmi%20Ford%2C%20a%20creator%20with%20242%2C000%20followers%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20saw%20many%20Black%20creators%20grow%20on%20TikTok%20when%20it%20boomed%20during%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20remember%20that%20phrase%2C%20'the%20democratization%20of%20influencing%2C'%20because%2C%20on%20Instagram%2C%20there%20weren't%20a%20lot%20of%20Black%20creators%20that%20had%20even%20hit%20a%20million%20followers%2C%26quot%3B%20Ford%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20got%20on%20TikTok%2C%20these%20same%20creators%2C%20with%20these%20same%20ideas%20and%20the%20same%20passion%2C%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20they're%20hitting%20millions%20of%20views%2C%20a%20million%20plus%20followers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20that%20the%20content%20wasn't%20good%2C%20Ford%20said%2C%20it%20was%20that%20Instagram%20%26quot%3Bjust%20wasn't%20a%20place%20for%20Black%20creators%2C%20minority%20creators%2C%20to%20excel.%26quot%3B%20On%20TikTok%2C%20in%20comparison%2C%20they%20%26quot%3Bgrew%20like%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%2019%25%20of%20TikTok%20users%20in%20the%20US%20are%20Black%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F04%2F03%2F6-facts-about-americans-and-tiktok%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20a%202023%20survey%20by%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20group's%20representation%20in%20the%20adult%20population%20(12%25).%20In%20the%20same%20report%2C%20while%2010%25%20of%20white%20teens%20said%20they%20used%20TikTok%20almost%20constantly%2C%2020%25%20of%20Black%20teens%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENya%20%C3%89tienne%2C%20a%20creator%20and%20journalist%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20turned%20to%20TikTok%20when%20she%20didn't%20feel%20heard%20in%20the%20traditional%20media%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%2C%20she%20was%20able%20to%20express%20herself%20and%20find%20her%20audience%2C%20she%20said.%20Rebuilding%20her%2026%2C000%20followers%20elsewhere%2C%20she%20said%2C%20would%20be%20a%20challenge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20looming%20TikTok%20ban%2C%20I've%20been%20trying%20to%20convert%20to%20Instagram%2C%20and%20it's%20going%20OK%2C%20but%20it's%20nothing%20like%20what%20I%20have%20on%20TikTok%2C%26quot%3B%20%C3%89tienne%20said.%20%26quot%3BTikTok%20is%20such%20a%20unique%20space%20for%20us%2C%20and%20it's%20sad%20that%20it%20could%20be%20taken%20away.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBlack-owned%20businesses%20thrive%20with%20TikTok%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfordeconomics.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTikTok_US_ExecSummary_March2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAn%20Oxford%20Economics%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20March%20found%20that%2057%25%20of%20small%20and%20medium%20Black-owned%20business%20owners%20said%20TikTok%20is%20%26quot%3Bcritical%20to%20their%20business's%20existence%2C%26quot%3B%20with%2083%25%20saying%20they%20had%20seen%20their%20sales%20increase%20after%20promoting%20their%20products%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFord%20said%20TikTok%20is%20full%20of%20mom%20and%20pop%20shops%20that%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bstruggling%20for%20years%26quot%3B%20that%20finally%20found%20a%20new%20audience%20and%20are%20now%20thriving.%20There%20are%20also%20popular%20influencers%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-keith-lee-became-tiktok-favorite-food-reviewer-in-months-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKeith%20Lee%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20highlight%20Black-owned%20small%20businesses%20and%20restaurants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20creators%20were%20also%20instrumental%20in%20pushing%20momentum%20on%20TikTok%20from%20a%20dance%20app%20to%20one%20full%20of%20conversations%2C%20entrepreneurialism%2C%20and%20personal%20stories%2C%20Ford%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBlack%20creators%20just%20did%20a%20lot%20to%20help%20the%20app%20be%20what%20it%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKahlil%20Dumas%2C%20a%20TikTok%20creator%20with%2029%2C000%20followers%20who%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20Free%20the%20CEO%20and%20the%20host%20of%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BUNSTUCKKD%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20if%20TikTok%20disappears%2C%20Black%20creators%20%26quot%3Brisk%20losing%20the%20communities%20they've%20built.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20would%20need%20to%20cultivate%20communities%20on%20other%20platforms%20while%20trying%20to%20transfer%20their%20TikTok%20community%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20not%20be%20easy%20to%20regrow%20their%20followings%20elsewhere%2C%20Dumas%20added%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20fewer%20brand%20deals%2C%20less%20ad%20revenue%2C%20and%20less%20income%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20complicated%20relationship%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20creators%20have%20a%20somewhat%20strained%20relationship%20with%20TikTok.%20Though%20the%20app%20has%20made%20efforts%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgetstarted.tiktok.com%2Fsupportblackbusinesses%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epromote%20Black-owned%20businesses%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20movements%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.tiktok.com%2Fen-us%2Fcelebrating-black-owned-businesses-during-blackbusinessmonth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%23BlackBusinessMonth%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2Fbusiness%2Fen-US%2Fblog%2Fsupport-black-owned-businesses-holiday-season%3Fredirected%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%23SupportBlack%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20Black%20creators%20have%20expressed%20frustrations%20with%20censorship%20and%20inequality%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Black%20creators%20suspected%20their%20Black%20Lives%20Matter%20content%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F5863350%2Ftiktok-black-creators%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20suppressed%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20George%20Floyd's%20death%20ignited%20a%20wave%20of%20protests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlack%20TikTokers%20have%20also%20expressed%20an%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-timeline-of-allegations-that-tiktok-censored-black-creators-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eundertone%20of%20anti-Blackness%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20platform's%20algorithm%2C%20where%20white%20creators%20benefited%20from%20the%20trends%20started%20by%20Black%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202020%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F02%2F13%2Fstyle%2Fthe-original-renegade.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20mega-popular%20%26quot%3BRenegade%26quot%3B%20dance%20on%20TikTok%20had%20been%20created%20by%20Jalaiah%20Harmon%2C%20a%20Black%20teenager%20from%20Atlanta%2C%20but%20everyone%20on%20the%20app%20seemed%20to%20attribute%20it%20to%20white%20TikTokers%20like%20Charli%20D'Amelio.%20White%20creators%20were%20also%20invited%20onto%20talk%20shows%20to%20demonstrate%20dances%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falors-on-danse-black-tiktokers-crediting-shadowbanning-race-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethat%20Black%20TikTokers%20came%20up%20with%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20TikTok%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20at%20the%20time%20that%20Black%20creators%20are%20%26quot%3Ba%20critical%20and%20vibrant%20part%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20experience%20on%20the%20app.%20%26quot%3BWe%20care%20deeply%20about%20the%20experience%20of%20Black%20creators%20on%20our%20platform%20and%20we%20continue%20to%20work%20every%20day%20to%20create%20a%20supportive%20environment%20for%20our%20community%20while%20also%20instilling%20a%20culture%20where%20honoring%20and%20crediting%20creators%20for%20their%20creative%20contributions%20is%20the%20norm%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%20have%20also%20shown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudy-black-influencers-make-significantly-less-money-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBlack%20creators%20make%20less%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20white%20counterparts%2C%20and%20it%20has%20taken%20longer%20for%20prominent%20Black%20creators%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmichiganchronicle.com%2Fno-black-creators-made-forbes-highest-paid-tiktokers-list%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20Khaby%20Lame%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20biggest%20creator%20on%20the%20platform%20with%20162%20million%20followers)%20to%20feature%20on%20Forbes'%20list%20of%20top-earning%20talent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20disheartening%2C%20Black%20creators%20told%20BI%2C%20because%20so%20many%20top%20trends%20and%20ideas%20come%20from%20their%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliams%20told%20BI%20TikTok's%20vibrancy%20and%20inclusivity%20of%20so%20many%20different%20cultures%20is%20thanks%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20ingenuity%2C%20authenticity%2C%20and%20trend-setting%20capacities%20of%20Black%20creators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20pioneers%20in%20carving%20the%20platform's%20soul